UNITED STATES of America v. GARBUTT OIL COMPANY. No. 8286. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 20, 1936. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and E. H. Mitchell, Sp. Asst, to U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal., for the United States. Claude I. Parker, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellant, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
